      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 85: The subscription is installed every time provideCode() reaches this path and is tied only to the view model\u0027s disposeBag. codeProvided prevents the common duplicate path, but if the flow is reused/reset without deallocation, old subscriptions remain active and can process future auth callbacks for the same account, including stale buffered state. Keep a dedicated disposable for the active add-device operation and dispose it before installing a new observer or when the operation reaches a terminal state.\n```suggestion\nprivate let authOperationDisposeBag \u003d SerialDisposable()\n\nlet disposable \u003d self.accountService.authStateSubject\n    .filter { [weak self] authResult in\n        guard let self \u003d self else { return false }\n        return authResult.accountId \u003d\u003d self.account.id\n    }\n    .observe(on: MainScheduler.instance)\n    .subscribe(onNext: { [weak self] authResult in\n        guard let self \u003d self else { return }\n        if self.operationId \u003d\u003d 0 {\n            self.pendingAuthResults.append(authResult)\n        } else if authResult.operationId \u003d\u003d self.operationId {\n            self.handleAuthResult(authResult)\n        }\n    })\nauthOperationDisposeBag.disposable \u003d disposable\n```",
