      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 252: start() now resets tempAccount and pendingAuthResults but does not cancel or disambiguate an already-running createTemporaryAccount() Task. If start() is invoked again before the previous Task completes, the older completion can later overwrite tempAccount and drain auth events for the wrong temporary account, reintroducing a race and potentially driving the UI with stale auth state. Track a generation/token or store and cancel the Task before starting a new one, then ignore completions that are no longer current.\n```suggestion\nprivate var startGeneration \u003d 0\nprivate var createAccountTask: Task\u003cVoid, Never\u003e?\n\nfunc start() {\n    uiState \u003d .initial\n    startGeneration +\u003d 1\n    let generation \u003d startGeneration\n    createAccountTask?.cancel()\n    tempAccount \u003d nil\n    pendingAuthResults.removeAll()\n    setupDeviceAuthObserver()\n\n    createAccountTask \u003d Task { [weak self] in\n        guard let self \u003d self else { return }\n        do {\n            let account \u003d try await self.accountsService.createTemporaryAccount()\n            await MainActor.run {\n                guard generation \u003d\u003d self.startGeneration else { return }\n                self.tempAccount \u003d account\n                let bufferedResults \u003d self.pendingAuthResults\n                self.pendingAuthResults.removeAll()\n                for result in bufferedResults where result.accountId \u003d\u003d account {\n                    self.updateDeviceAuthState(result: result)\n                }\n            }\n        } catch {\n            await MainActor.run {\n                guard generation \u003d\u003d self.startGeneration else { return }\n                withAnimation { self.uiState \u003d .error(message: LinkDeviceError.networkError) }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n```",
